item.description:
Arrays are a fixed-size sequence of objects. In Mita, arrays can hold any type:
var array1 : array&lt;int32&gt;; struct vec2d { var x : int32; var y : int32; } let array2 : array&lt;vec2d&gt;; Initialization There are multiple ways to initialize and fill arrays:
let array1 : array&lt;int32&gt; = new array&lt;int32&gt;(size = 10); let array2 : array&lt;int32&gt; = [1,2,3,4]; Length Mita arrays know how long arrays are, unlike C arrays.
